spec: uuid_extra153
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra152.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__dict__ membership checks using __contains__ and __class__.__name__/__len__() (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra151.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ qualname strings and lengths; ordering dunder qualname length ordering (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra150.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID property fget qualnames: hex.fget.__qualname__/__eq__ / bytes.fget.__qualname__ / version.fget.__qualname__ / variant.fget.__qualname__ / urn.fget.__qualname__ / fields.fget.__qualname__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra149.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__init__/__qualname__/__code__.co_argcount==7/__code__.co_name / __str__/__repr__/__hash__/__eq__ co_name and co_argcount ordering (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra147.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') / UUID.__slots__.__len__()==3 / UUID.__hash__/__str__/__repr__/__eq__ qualname lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid.zspec / early extras — cover uuid.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in uuid_extra86 through uuid_extra152."
    - "Wave 343 theme: uuid.UUID.__slots__ attribute details — UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('tuple') / UUID.__slots__.__len__()==3 / UUID.__slots__.__contains__('int') / UUID.__slots__.__contains__('is_safe') / UUID.__slots__.__contains__('__weakref__'); extra147 anchors __slots__.__class__.__name__ and __len__() as rows; this spec anchors __contains__ checks and provides them all as combined tables with standalone invariants."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__class__.__name__ == 'tuple'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__len__() == 3. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('int') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('is_safe') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('__weakref__') == True. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__slots__ == ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__'). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__slots__ == ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__') — a 3-element tuple. __slots__ is defined in Lib/uuid.py as: __slots__ = ('int', 'is_safe', '__weakref__'). The three slots serve distinct purposes: 'int' stores the 128-bit integer value of the UUID (the core data); 'is_safe' stores a SafeUUID enum value indicating whether the UUID was generated safely; '__weakref__' enables weak references to UUID instances. extra147 anchors __slots__.__class__.__name__=='tuple' and __slots__.__len__()==3 as table rows; those are confirmed but the __contains__ checks for individual slot names are novel."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('int') == True. The 'int' slot stores the UUID as a 128-bit integer. UUID.int is a member_descriptor (not a property; extra145 anchors UUID.int.__class__.__name__=='member_descriptor'). Accessing uuid_obj.int returns the 128-bit integer representation. The 'int' slot is listed first in the __slots__ tuple."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('is_safe') == True. The 'is_safe' slot stores a SafeUUID enum value. UUID(is_safe=SafeUUID.safe) indicates the UUID was generated by a safe method. SafeUUID.safe has value 0, SafeUUID.unknown has value -1. The 'is_safe' slot is listed second in the __slots__ tuple."
    - "Note: uuid.UUID.__slots__.__contains__('__weakref__') == True. The '__weakref__' slot is required to enable weak references to UUID instances. Without '__weakref__' in __slots__, instances of a class with __slots__ cannot be weakly referenced. '__weakref__' is listed third (last) in the __slots__ tuple."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
